Introductie
Client Services | Financial Markets | Trade Transactions | Operations | Financial Products | Banking | International | BSc / MSc | Amsterdam | € 2.800 – € 3.000 gross per month (40 hours per week)
Have you completed your Bachelor or Master and are you looking for a starting position within the financial sector? Would you like to work in a highly dynamic and international organization? Do you have strong analytical and communication skills and affinity with financial markets? The position as Junior Client Trade Officer might be interesting for you! Please read on for more information.

Organisatie
Our client is a leading global player in Financial Markets services. They provide professional investors (including professional traders, market makers, brokers and investment parties) access to financial markets and make it possible for these clients to trade in financial products. Furthermore, these investors are supported in complying with law and regulations.

Functie
As Junior Client Trade Officer you are part of the Client Operations team. Client Operations is the entry point to the client for all operational queries. Currently, this business line is in transition. Focus is on digitization, automation of processes and data driven innovation. This leads to a need for ‘new generation’ employees with an innovative mindset.
Responsibilities:
Client contact on a daily basis and helping the client with trade related queries with regard to the full range of the business (Clearing, Settlements, and Reconciliations). Whether by phone, in writing or face to face, you represent the bank and maintain the highest levels of professionalism at all times;
Using innovative thinking you will assist in the continuous improvement of the service;
Networking with various other departments, to ensure the best solutions and service to the clients;
Participation in data analytics en process improvement projects;
You will work through Agile principles and participate in daily stand up meetings and sprints.

Functie-eisen
To be successful as Junior Client Trade Officer, the following should apply:
A Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in economics, business economics, business administration or similar;
0 – 2 years of working experience;
Knowledge of financials products and banking;
Strong communication skills;
Real listener and problem solver;
Emphatic, proactive and hands-on mentality;
Excellent in English, spoken and written.

Aanbod
As Junior Client Trade Officer, we offer you:
A challenging job in a highly dynamic and international environment;
Learning on the job from experienced colleagues;
You learn to professionally and effectively communicate with clients, other teams and departments, which allows you to build up a valuable network;
You will get insight into various banking processes, systems, products and regulations of one of the most professional players in the financial markets;
Great career opportunities within the bank.
Young Financials offers you:
Excellent primary and secondary benefits;
€ 2.800 – €3.000,- gross per month (40 hours per week), depending on knowledge and experience;
Extra study budget of € 750 for external education and / or training courses;
24 annual holidays plus paid public holidays;
8% holiday allowance;
Full commuting allowance.

Sollicitatie
 If you wish to receive more information about this job opening, please contact Noortje Slagter via +31 20 489 23 20 or send an e-mail torecruitment@youngfinancials.com

Can you further accelerate the growth of our EV charging network for EV charging - being one of the largest of Europe - to ensure the best possible coverage and most competitive pricing in Europe? Do you combine a solid experience of selling and buying services in technology oriented and a rapidly growing industry? Do you truly believe in the strength of teamwork? We might be looking for you!

WE ARE NEWMOTION

We are Europe’s largest electric charging partner. We are on a mission to enable everybody to drive as many kilometers as possible powered by clean energy. We do that by offering large scale smart charging solutions to the masses. We contribute to a low-carbon world by making EV charging easy, accessible and smart, with the best expertise, highest quality & service.
WHAT YOU’LL BE IN CHARGE OF

NewMotion provides leading Customer Value Propositions for EV charging at home, at the office or when on the go. Part of our service offering consists of enabling public charging, both on our own chargepoint network as well as on the networks of others (‘roaming’) for our customers.

As Manager EV Charging Europe you will have the responsibility for the roaming network of NewMotion - the largest EV Charging network in Europe with 170 thousand chargers - and you are tasked with a.o. acquisition of new roaming partners, management of existing partners, commercial conditions including pricing, monitoring and enhancing the quality of services. Additionally, you will be responsible for selling access to the NewMotion managed charge point network to third parties eMobility Service Providers. You will be tasked with the management of the roaming team consisting of a roaming Manager and a charge point data manager.
We are looking for a Manager EV Charging Europe that will enable the next phase of growth of our Roaming network and further enhance our competitive position. to head the roaming team. This team is part of the Roaming and Driver Services department. The department is responsible for the commercial activities, proposition management, commercial project management and product development and is focusing on end-users, corporate and wholesale customers.

THIS IS HOW YOU’LL CONTRIBUTE

To extend and optimize the NewMotion roaming network, a key differentiator to our public charging services;
Contract negotiations including roaming tariffs and conditions;
Represent NewMotion in the country specific industry associations including for example task groups such as pricing transparency;
Roaming contracts administration and management;
Management of roaming tariffs (business to business and end-user);
Responsible introduction of new and updated partnerships, tariff changes, etc;
Driver Data (POI information) of the NewMotion roaming charge point network;
Monitor the market and provide insights;
Subject Matter Expert and support the organisation with relevant info (Sales tenders, Customer Support, etc);
Work closely with the product - and proposition managers to further develop the roaming services;
Management of Charge Point Data Managers and Partner Managers;
Motivate and guide direct reports to optimize the knowledge and performance level;
Performing development plan of direct reports to ensure further development..

THIS IS WHO YOU ARE

Master degree in Engineering, Business, Economics or similar;
At least 5 -7 years experience in a comparable position or 10 years in a similar type of industry e.g. telco -, internet -, financial - or mobility service sector with extensive experience with:
Relationship management;
Sales
B2B Purchasing;
Regulatory
Contract negotiation on European/ international level;
Strong communicator;
Experiences with people management, preferable 2 to 3 years;
Have or develop a deep understanding of the EV-roaming market (commercial / strategic terms, technical possibilities, legal/regulatory);
Experience reviewing/preparing contracts;
Quickly understands a highly complex product & market, both from a technology as from a business point of view.
Comfortable in relating and coordinating with different departments, from developers to finance and update at different levels in the organization
Language requirements: Fluent English is a must and German, French, Dutch are preferred.
Result driven and able to work with tight deadlines.
Location flexibility including regular travel to the Netherlands (post Covid)

BECOME PART OF THE CHANGE
Working at NewMotion means working in a fun, fast-growing international company with big ambitions.
By joining us, you will:

Contribute to a more sustainable future;
Become an expert in e-mobility;
Work in an open and transparent culture with colleagues from all over the world;
Receive a competitive salary that fits your experience + bonus;
Receive a MacBook;
Enjoy daily healthy lunches, prepared by our masterchefs;
Develop your skills and expertise through several trainings. Besides this, you will receive a personal training budget and set your annual goals with your personal development plan;
Enjoy our fun weekly get-togethers (drinks), our annual winter and summer outing, NewMotion running team on the Dam tot Damloop, or any other event initiated by colleagues!

