About GRESB
GRESB was launched eleven years ago by a group of large pension funds who wanted to have a better engagement with their managers on sustainability issues. In the intervening years, we have grown to become the leading Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) benchmark for real estate and infrastructure investments across the world.
Our ESG data and benchmarks now cover over USD 4.5 trillion in real estate and infrastructure value and are used by more than 100 institutional investors to make decisions that lead to a more sustainable world.
We have an engaged community of asset managers who are proud to participate in our annual benchmarking process and a group of inspirational industry partners and ESG service providers who amplify our reach.
The GRESB team comes from diverse backgrounds with experience spanning sustainability, data science, software development, real estate, infrastructure, and the capital markets. We’re passionate about tackling the sustainability challenge by providing insights that will power the markets of the future and enable investors to allocate the world’s capital in a more responsible way.
We are an energetic group of 30+ people, covering dozens of different nationalities, located in Amsterdam, with satellite offices in Washington DC and Sydney. We care deeply about creating a positive and inclusive working environment where everyone feels comfortable contributing their ideas.
Responsibilities
Marketing & Communications:
Updating and maintaining the gresb.com website via Wordpress, including Partner directory and event calendar
Event and partner promotion through social media
Working with partners on the publication of content on our blog GRESB Insights
Supporting the use of Salesforce (CRM) and Pardot (integrated marketing tool)
Helpdesk
Member logo maintenance
Events & Training:
Assistance with marketing, logistics and partner collaborations for the 2021 GRESB Results events
Maintaining our master events-tracking sheet
Requirements
You are currently pursuing a Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in a field related to Marketing, Business, Management, Administration, or Communications. Applicants who are not students during the internship will not be considered;
You are eligible to work in the EU and have a visa (Unfortunately, we cannot sponsor you for an EU work permit for this position);
You have good collaboration skills;
You have a native-level of written and spoken English;
You are very well organized, self-sufficient and able to work in a busy, international environment;
You have a high degree of comfort using common software packages and online tools (Excel, Word, Powerpoint). Experience of using design software, Wordpress is a plus; CSS is plus;
Benefits
Involvement in a dynamic international organization, that has become the leading sustainability benchmark for real assets;
Opportunity to work with a highly talented team in a supportive environment with loads of camaraderie;
Autonomy and the chance to take responsibility for tasks from the beginning of your internship;
The opportunity to develop your network by being involved with all types of GRESB stakeholders (Investors, fund managers, sustainability consultants and industry bodies);
You will develop experience in office management, including using Salesforce – the world's leading Customer Relationship Management (CRM) solutions – and Pardot;
Hungry? We provide a free and healthy lunch at the office;
Need to commute? You will enjoy free public transport to and from work inside the Netherlands.

